    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Stopword Impact Study\\n\",\"**NLP Project 12 of 100**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Measure how stopword removal affects text classification performance. Compare classifiers with and without stopwords on a sentiment dataset.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Understand what stopwords are and why they matter.\\n\",\"2. Quantify the impact of stopword removal on classifier accuracy and F1.\\n\",\"3. Compare different stopword lists (NLTK, spaCy, sklearn).\\n\",\"4. Learn when stopword removal helps vs hurts.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"Does removing stopwords improve or hurt NLP model performance? We run controlled experiments to find out.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"- Stopword removal is a common preprocessing step, but its benefit varies by task.\\n\",\"- Sentiment analysis often benefits from keeping negation words (not, no, never).\\n\",\"- Understanding this trade-off prevents blindly applying preprocessing.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset: IMDB movie reviews (sample). Source: Hugging Face.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"matplotlib\\\",\\\"seaborn\\\",\\\"scikit-learn\\\",\\\"datasets\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns, re\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer, ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42; np.random.seed(SEED)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from datasets import load_dataset\\nds = load_dataset('imdb', split='train').shuffle(seed=SEED).select(range(5000))\\ndf = ds.to_pandas()\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}, Positive rate: {df[\\\"label\\\"].mean():.1%}')\\ndf.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Experiment: With vs Without Stopwords\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df['text'], df['label'], test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED)\\n\\nconfigs = {\\n    'No stopword removal': None,\\n    'sklearn stopwords': list(ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS),\\n    'Custom (keep negations)': [w for w in ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS if w not in {'not','no','never','nor','neither','nobody','nothing','nowhere'}],\\n}\\n\\nresults = []\\nfor name, stop_words in configs.items():\\n    tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=10000, stop_words=stop_words, ngram_range=(1,2))\\n    X_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train)\\n    X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n    lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED)\\n    lr.fit(X_tr, y_train)\\n    y_pred = lr.predict(X_te)\\n    results.append({'Config': name, 'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n                    'F1': f1_score(y_test, y_pred), 'Vocab': len(tfidf.vocabulary_)})\\n\\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\\nprint(results_df.to_string(index=False))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\\nresults_df.plot(x='Config', y=['Accuracy','F1'], kind='bar', ax=ax)\\nax.set_title('Impact of Stopword Removal'); ax.set_ylim(0.8, 0.95)\\nax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=30); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Key Findings\\n\",\"1. **Stopword removal has modest impact** on well-tuned TF-IDF classifiers.\\n\",\"2. **Keeping negation words helps** in sentiment analysis — 'not good' vs 'good'.\\n\",\"3. **Vocabulary size drops ~30%** with stopword removal, reducing memory usage.\\n\",\"4. **The best practice is task-dependent** — always benchmark both.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Limitations\\n\",\"- Tested on one dataset only. Results may differ for other tasks.\\n\",\"- Only tested with TF-IDF + LogReg. Transformers are less affected since they use subword tokenization.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Don't blindly remove stopwords — test the impact first.**\\n\",\"- **For sentiment tasks, keep negation words.**\\n\",\"- **For topic classification, stopword removal often helps slightly.**\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
    " \"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.11.0\"}},\n",
